summary: human coronaviruses (HCoVs) are enveloped viruses within the family Coronaviridae with positive-sense, single-stranded genomes of up to 32 kb. the 5′ two-thirds of the genome encodes the large replicases 1a and 1b encoding nonstructural proteins. the 3′ one-third encodes the structural proteins (1). cDNA was synthesized with SuperScript III reverse transcriptase (Invitrogen) with random hexamers. cDNA was synthesized with Klenow polymerase (5 U; New England BioLabs) libraries were prepared using the Nextera XT kit (Illumina) according to the manufacturer’s instructions.
